═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 0 — CREATE THE WORKSPACE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Run:
mkdir -p ~/Japan-hack
mkdir -p ~/Japan-hack/.claude
mkdir -p ~/Japan-hack/docs/archive

cd ~/Japan-hack
pwd

Expected output: /Users/[username]/Japan-hack
STATUS: PASS if pwd shows Japan-hack, FAIL otherwise.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 1 — VERIFY SYSTEM PREREQUISITES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Check each tool. If missing, install it. Do not skip.

STEP 1A — Homebrew
Run: brew --version
If missing:
  /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
Expected: Homebrew 4.x.x or higher

STEP 1B — Node.js (v18 minimum)
Run: node --version
If missing or below v18:
  brew install node
Expected: v18.x.x or higher

STEP 1C — npm
Run: npm --version
Expected: 9.x.x or higher (comes with Node)

STEP 1D — Python 3
Run: python3 --version
If missing:
  brew install python3
Expected: Python 3.10 or higher

STEP 1E — pip3
Run: pip3 --version
If missing:
  python3 -m ensurepip --upgrade
Expected: pip 23.x or higher

STEP 1F — Git
Run: git --version
If missing:
  brew install git
Expected: git version 2.x.x

STEP 1G — curl
Run: curl --version
Expected: curl 7.x or 8.x — already on macOS, no install needed

STEP 1H — Rust toolchain
Run: rustc --version
If missing:
  curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y
  source $HOME/.cargo/env
Expected: rustc 1.7x.x or higher

STEP 1I — Claude Code CLI
Run: claude --version
If missing: stop and print:
  "Claude Code is not installed. Install it from https://claude.ai/code 
   then re-run this prompt."
  Do NOT attempt to install Claude Code yourself.
Expected: claude x.x.x

